    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-03T06:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-03T06:30:00-05:00" n="257"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/7–350: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grady</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-03T15:00:00+03:30"
                            >July 3, 1950—3 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. Prime Minister Razmara told Embassy official Saturday he considers <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>s action re
                    Korea “splendid” and thinks that Soviet bluff has been effectively called.
                    Razmara’s opinion generally reflected Iran officialdom and press.</p>
                <p>Shah told me yesterday Iran heartened by evidence US prepared support small
                    nations when confronted by armed Communist aggression. He obviously had idea in
                    mind that time might come when he would need such assistance.</p>
                <pb facs="0586" n="564" xml:id="pg_564"/>
                <p>Department inform Army, Navy, Air.</p>
                <p>Department pass Moscow. Sent Department 16, repeated Moscow 3.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grady</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
